{
  "stem": "1858.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we tried somehow in concentration camp to remember holidays or Shabbat, not that we had a calendar to go by--",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Observe?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was no way of observing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But you know what?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "On Yom Kippur, which is a day of fast by the Jewish people, this was the time that, if ever, we were given better food or a little bit more or a piece of meat, it would be on Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they would keep that in mind that it is that day that we are not supposed to eat.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they would try to give us food to discourage us from fasting.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Although many girls did fast, I did not.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was not that courageous.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was too hungry to think of the holiday.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But somehow, many of the girls did observe the holidays or try to remember or try to say a prayer, though it was almost impossible.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Many times we would come from work hungry, cold, tired.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We would be called to [GERMAN], which meant roll call, where we would be forced to stand outdoors in all kinds of weather.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And while standing there, our Nazi guards would think about ways of humiliating us, degrading us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They would squeeze out of us the last reserves of human dignity.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "These guards were males as well as females.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were human beings.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "After the war, many of them during the Nazi trials tried to claim that they followed orders.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But they did not because Hitler was not in our concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Hitler was not there telling them what to do.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "How does a human being become a beast?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What makes him do such things to others?",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
